: Eastern and Western Ways of Dealing with the Bali Bombings -- tPart IV Instrumentalizing Repositories of Memory -- tChapter 12 September 11 Museums, Spontaneous Memorials, and History -- tChapter 13 Piazza Carlo Giuliani— G8 Summit, Genoa 2001 Death, Testimony, Memory -- tChapter 14 Memorializing a Controversial Politician: The “Heritagization” of a Materialized Vox Populi -- tNotes on Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGrassroots memorials have become major areas of focus during times of trauma, danger, and social unrest. These improvised memorial assemblages continue to display new and more dynamic ways of representing collective and individual identities and in doing so reveal the steps that shape the national memories of those who struggle to come to terms with traumatic loss. This volume focuses on the hybrid quality of these temporary memorials as both monuments of mourning and as focal points for protest and expression of discontent. The broad range of case studies in this volume include anti-mafia shrines, Theo van Gogh’s memorial, September 11th memorials, March 11th shrines in Madrid, and Carlo Giuliani memorials in Genoa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aDeathxSocial aspects. 0aMemorialization. 0aSocial movementsxPolitical aspects. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 21st Century.2bisacsh1 aCaffarena, Fabio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobler, Robert Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFraenkel, Béatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, James B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrider, Sylvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c